HEADWORD: Catachresis
<hw>Cat`a*chre"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. fr. Gr. <?/
misuse, fr. <?/ to misuse; <grk>kata`</grk> against + <?/ to use.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure by which one word is wrongly put for
another, or by which a word is wrested from its true signification; as,
⟦ldquo⟧To take arms against a sea of troubles⟦rdquo⟧. <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Her voice was but the shadow of a sound.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Young.</au></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

